fields.content:
# Knightcycle Updates!

Its been an incredibly busy week as I start putting the pieces in place for what could soon become the official launch of **Knightcycle**. The more I dig into it, the clearer it becomes that this idea is both *viable* and *genuinely needed*.

The support from the 3D printing community has been amazing  hobbyists, small businesses, and makerspaces have all shown real passion for sustainability and recycling. Its clear theres a strong demand for what Knightcycle aims to do.

---

## Whats Been Happening

- Securing sustainable material suppliers and testing masterbatch samples  
- Designing and prototyping cardboard filament spools (with some laser-engraving fun along the way!)  
- Sorting out logistics, including potential couriers and collection options  
- Setting up tools for testing and sorting plastics for recycling  
- Exploring promising locations for Knightcycles first base of operations  
- Accepting donated scrap PLA for initial recycling trials  
- Refining the business model to make startup leaner and more sustainable  

---

## Whats Next

The focus now is to reach out to local businesses and makerspaces to gauge interest in a **Knightcycle subscription model**  a key step in helping the project get off the ground. Once the first partners sign on, the initial investment phase can begin, and full-scale filament testing will kick off.

Im also planning to consult with environmental experts to ensure every aspect of Knightcycle meets sustainability standards and waste regulations.

Theres a lot ahead, but its all feeling more real every day.
